After hesitating a moment, Cody moved on in the direction he had been heading. "Probably just Lulu making friends with one of
the locals," he said, fingering a dart nervously. The sounds suddenly intensified, then seemed to move off into the distance.
Cody winced. "Hope it wasn't anyone friendly." The thought momentarily crossed his mind that Lulu might be in trouble, a
thought he immediately dismissed as far too great a thing to hope.
